body:
# Block Kit

Block Kit is Slack's UI framework for composing rich, interactive messages. Messages are built from stackable **blocks**, each containing **elements** and **composition objects**. Block Kit is used everywhere: [[slack/messages]], [[slack/bots]] responses, [[slack/webhooks]] payloads, and modal views.

## Blocks

Blocks are the top-level layout containers. Stack them to build a message:

| Block | Purpose | Example |
|-------|---------|---------|
| `section` | Text with optional accessory (button, image, menu) | Main content |
| `header` | Large bold text | Title |
| `divider` | Horizontal line | Visual separator |
| `actions` | Row of interactive elements | Button group |
| `context` | Small text and images | Metadata, timestamps |
| `input` | Form input (modals only) | Text field, select |
| `image` | Full-width image | Charts, screenshots |
| `rich_text` | Rich text with formatting | Formatted content |

```json
{
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "header",
      "text": { "type": "plain_text", "text": "Deploy Report" }
    },
    { "type": "divider" },
    {
      "type": "section",
      "text": {
        "type": "mrkdwn",
        "text": "*Service:* `api-gateway`\n*Status:* :white_check_mark: Success\n*Duration:* 3m 42s"
      },
      "accessory": {
        "type": "button",
        "text": { "type": "plain_text", "text": "View Logs" },
        "url": "https://example.com/logs",
        "action_id": "view_logs"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "context",
      "elements": [
        { "type": "mrkdwn", "text": "Deployed by <@U0123456> | main branch | commit `a1b2c3d`" }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

## Elements

Elements are the interactive and display components inside blocks:

| Element | Type | Used In |
|---------|------|---------|
| Button | `button` | section, actions |
| Static select | `static_select` | section, actions, input |
| External select | `external_select` | section, actions, input |
| Multi-select | `multi_static_select` | section, actions, input |
| Date picker | `datepicker` | section, actions, input |
| Time picker | `timepicker` | actions, input |
| Plain text input | `plain_text_input` | input |
| Checkbox group | `checkboxes` | section, actions, input |
| Radio buttons | `radio_buttons` | section, actions, input |
| Overflow menu | `overflow` | section, actions |
| Image | `image` | section, context |

All interactive elements need an `action_id` for handling responses. See [[slack/bots#interactions]] for wiring up handlers.

## Composition Objects

Composition objects are reusable structures used within blocks and elements:

- **Text object** — `{ type: "mrkdwn", text: "..." }` or `{ type: "plain_text", text: "..." }`. mrkdwn supports Slack formatting (see [[slack/messages#formatting]]).
- **Confirm dialog** — `{ title, text, confirm, deny }` — attach to any interactive element for user confirmation before action.
- **Option object** — `{ text, value, description }` — used in selects, checkboxes, and radio buttons.
- **Option group** — `{ label, options }` — group related options in select menus.
- **Filter object** — filter conversation lists by type (public, private, DM, mpim).

```json
{
  "type": "button",
  "text": { "type": "plain_text", "text": "Delete" },
  "style": "danger",
  "action_id": "delete_item",
  "confirm": {
    "title": { "type": "plain_text", "text": "Are you sure?" },
    "text": { "type": "mrkdwn", "text": "This action cannot be undone." },
    "confirm": { "type": "plain_text", "text": "Delete" },
    "deny": { "type": "plain_text", "text": "Cancel" }
  }
}
```

## Actions Block

The `actions` block holds up to 25 interactive elements in a horizontal row:

```json
{
  "type": "actions",
  "elements": [
    {
      "type": "button",
      "text": { "type": "plain_text", "text": "Approve" },
      "style": "primary",
      "action_id": "approve_request"
    },
    {
      "type": "button",
      "text": { "type": "plain_text", "text": "Reject" },
      "style": "danger",
      "action_id": "reject_request"
    },
    {
      "type": "static_select",
      "placeholder": { "type": "plain_text", "text": "Assign to..." },
      "action_id": "assign_request",
      "options": [
        { "text": { "type": "plain_text", "text": "Alice" }, "value": "U001" },
        { "text": { "type": "plain_text", "text": "Bob" }, "value": "U002" }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

## Modals

Modals are popup views with input forms. Opened via `views.open` with a `trigger_id` from a command or interaction:

```json
{
  "type": "modal",
  "callback_id": "create_ticket",
  "title": { "type": "plain_text", "text": "New Ticket" },
  "submit": { "type": "plain_text", "text": "Create" },
  "close": { "type": "plain_text", "text": "Cancel" },
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "input",
      "block_id": "title_block",
      "element": {
        "type": "plain_text_input",
        "action_id": "title_input"
      },
      "label": { "type": "plain_text", "text": "Title" }
    },
    {
      "type": "input",
      "block_id": "priority_block",
      "element": {
        "type": "static_select",
        "action_id": "priority_select",
        "options": [
          { "text": { "type": "plain_text", "text": "Low" }, "value": "low" },
          { "text": { "type": "plain_text", "text": "Medium" }, "value": "medium" },
          { "text": { "type": "plain_text", "text": "High" }, "value": "high" }
        ]
      },
      "label": { "type": "plain_text", "text": "Priority" }
    },
    {
      "type": "input",
      "block_id": "desc_block",
      "element": {
        "type": "plain_text_input",
        "action_id": "desc_input",
        "multiline": true
      },
      "label": { "type": "plain_text", "text": "Description" },
      "optional": true
    }
  ]
}
```

Handle submissions with `app.view("create_ticket", handler)` in [[slack/bots#interactions]]. Access values at `view.state.values[block_id][action_id].value`.

## Block Kit Builder

Use the visual builder at https://app.slack.com/block-kit-builder to:

- Drag and drop blocks to compose layouts
- Preview messages as they will appear in Slack
- Copy the generated JSON payload
- Test with sample data

Paste the generated JSON into your `blocks` array in [[slack/messages]], [[slack/webhooks]], or [[slack/bots]] code.
